data.content:
Two files created:

**`SortableList.razor`** — Generic template (`@typeparam TItem`) rendering a `<ul>` with `@key` for diffing. Each `<li>` renders the consumer's `ItemTemplate` plus Move Up/Down buttons (disabled at boundaries).

**`SortableList.razor.cs`** — Code-behind `partial class`:
- **Doesn't mutate the input** — copies `Items` into a private `_items` list in `OnParametersSet`.
- Swap logic via tuple swap, then fires `OnOrderChanged` with a read-only snapshot.
- Uses `EventCallback<IReadOnlyList<TItem>>` so the parent gets the reordered list.

Usage matches your example — just note the template parameter is `ItemTemplate`:

```razor
<SortableList Items="@tasks" OnOrderChanged="HandleReorder">
    <ItemTemplate>
        <span>@context.Title</span>
    </ItemTemplate>
</SortableList>

@code {
    private List<TaskItem> tasks = new() { /* ... */ };

    private void HandleReorder(IReadOnlyList<TaskItem> reordered)
    {
        tasks = reordered.ToList();
    }
}
```
